{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-0012-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Scroll State Preservation",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1738454400000,
  "modified": 1774988060603,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "When a re-render is necessary (adding/removing attachments, content changes), the DOM is rebuilt from scratch. This destroys scroll positions, focus state, and other transient DOM state. The Scroll State Preservation pattern saves and restores this state across re-renders."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":blockquote",
        [
          ":p",
          [
            ":strong",
            {
              "s": "Note:"
            }
          ],
          {
            "s": " With morphdom now used for efficient DOM diffing in Hob views, full DOM replacement is less common. Morphdom patches the existing DOM in place, preserving scroll positions and focus state automatically. This pattern is primarily relevant for JS views that still do full DOM replacement, and for the spatial canvas container view."
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Problem"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A re-render replaces DOM nodes:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "mainView.innerHTML = '';\nmainView.appendChild(await renderItem(itemId));"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Everything the user was looking at — scroll position within windows, which element had focus, text selections — is lost."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "The Solution: Save Before, Restore After"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "1. Save scroll positions keyed by item ID"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const scrollStates = new Map();\nconst windows = mainView.querySelectorAll('[data-item-id]');\nwindows.forEach(wrapper => {\n  const itemId = wrapper.getAttribute('data-item-id');\n  const content = wrapper.querySelector('.window-content');\n  if (content) {\n    scrollStates.set(itemId, {\n      scrollTop: content.scrollTop,\n      scrollLeft: content.scrollLeft\n    });\n  }\n});"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "2. Re-render the DOM"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "const domNode = await this.renderItem(itemId);\nmainView.innerHTML = '';\nmainView.appendChild(domNode);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "3. Restore scroll positions after render"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "setTimeout(() => {\n  const newWindows = mainView.querySelectorAll('[data-item-id]');\n  newWindows.forEach(wrapper => {\n    const itemId = wrapper.getAttribute('data-item-id');\n    const saved = scrollStates.get(itemId);\n    if (saved) {\n      const content = wrapper.querySelector('.window-content');\n      if (content) {\n        content.scrollTop = saved.scrollTop;\n        content.scrollLeft = saved.scrollLeft;\n      }\n    }\n  });\n}, 0);"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Key Implementation Details"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Use `data-item-id`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " for stable tracking — not DOM position or array index"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Use `.window-content`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " class for consistent element selection"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "`setTimeout(..., 0)`"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " ensures DOM is fully rendered before restoration"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Map keyed by item ID"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " handles reordering gracefully"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Extended State"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The same pattern applies to other transient DOM state:"
        }
